HIGHER PENSION AND POST-RETIREMENT AMOUNTS IN 2005 COMPARED TO 2004 ARE PRIMARILY

RELATED TO HIGHER AMORTIZATION OF ACTUARIAL LOSSES AND NET SETTLEMENT AND CURTAILMENT CHARGES DUE TO 2005 DIVESTITURES. THE INCREASE IN 2005 SHARE-BASED PLANS EXPENSE IS PRIMARILY DUE TO THE INCREASE IN OUR STOCK PRICE WHICH RESULTED IN ADDITIONAL

COMPENSATION EXPENSE DUE TO AN INCREASE IN THE NUMBER OF PERFORMANCE SHARES MEETING THE PRICE GROWTH TARGETS AND BEING CONVERTED TO COMMON STOCK.

