UNBILLABLE RECEIVABLES ON

LONG-TERM CONTRACTS ARISE WHEN THE SALES OR REVENUES BASED ON PERFORMANCE ATTAINMENT, THOUGH APPROPRIATELY RECOGNIZED, CANNOT BE BILLED YET UNDER TERMS OF THE CONTRACT AS OF THE BALANCE SHEET DATE. ACCOUNTS RECEIVABLE RELATED TO CLAIMS ARE ITEMS

THAT WE BELIEVE ARE EARNED, BUT ARE SUBJECT TO UNCERTAINTY CONCERNING THEIR DETERMINATION OR ULTIMATE REALIZATION. ACCOUNTS RECEIVABLE, OTHER THAN THOSE DESCRIBED ABOVE, EXPECTED TO BE COLLECTED AFTER ONE YEAR ARE NOT MATERIAL.

